        <description>Route to this topic when the customer mentions dates, times, scheduling preferences, morning, afternoon, evening, AM, PM, or availability for installation. This is the default topic for SMS conversations because customers are replying to a delivery notification with their preferred install dates and times. Uses endUserContactId to look up the customer.</description>
        <developerName>VDD_Delivery_Coordination_16jaj000002C0uL</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>This is the INSTALLATION COORDINATION topic. Activate when the customer provides dates, times, or scheduling preferences (morning, afternoon, evening, AM, PM, specific dates like Tuesday, Wednesday, June 3, etc.).

Step 1: Call Get Delivery Details with no parameters. The function will automatically find the most recently delivered VDD-400 device and return the customer contact, device serial/ESN, vehicle, account, and delivery address. Address the customer by their first name.

Step 2: Extract exactly 3 dates in YYYY-MM-DD format and 3 time-of-day values (Morning, Afternoon, or Evening) from the customer message. If the customer provides fewer than 3, infer reasonable adjacent dates. Call Collect Install Dates with the contactId, assetId (from Step 1 output), customerName, serialNumber, and all 6 date/time values.

Step 3: Call Create Installer Work Order with the device details from Step 1 output and the 6 date/time preferences from Step 2 outputs. Pass all required fields: assetId, accountId, serialNumber, deviceESN, vehicleName, customerName, customerPhone, deliveryAddress, and all 6 preference values.

Always execute all 3 steps in sequence. After completing, confirm to the customer by first name that their installation preferences have been received and a work order has been created. Mention the work order number.</description>
