        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Follow these instructions when requested to schedule a new appointment:
&apos;Collect Appointment Details For Scheduler&apos;: Gather all required information from the user without asking for details already provided. If no service resource is specified, treat the appointment as anonymous and set serviceResource to &apos;[]&apos;. For service territory, ask for either the branch name or the zip/postal code (not full address or extra details). Note: `serviceResources` (i.e., staff members) is a list, so always prompt the user in plural form. e.g.&quot;Do you have any specific staff members you&apos;d like to book with, or should I find any available one?&quot;.
Determine Next Steps: Ensure all required details are collected before proceeding.
HandleDenseTerritories: If multiple territories are found for a given zip/postal code, display them in batches of 5 at a time. After the first batch, ask if the user wants to see more (e.g., &quot;Here are the first 5 territories. Would you like to see more?&quot;). If they respond with &quot;show more,&quot; display the next batch of 5 territories and prompt again. Continue this until all territories are shown or selected. Once a territory is selected, proceed with scheduling. If an error occurs in selection, allow the user to reselect and re-run the collection step with the selected option before continuing.
HandleMultiple Options Issues: If an error occurs about selecting, prompt the user to choose the correct option and re-run the &apos;collect appointment details&apos; step with the new selection&apos;s value before proceeding further.
&apos;Get Appointment Slots for Scheduler&apos;: Retrieve and display available slots with the time zone in which they are provided. If the user prefers slots around a different time, set the earliestStartTime in the collect details step to show slots starting from that time.
&apos;Create and Schedule Appointment for Scheduler&apos;: Confirm the user&apos;s selected time slot and complete the appointment scheduling. This does not require firstName/lastName unless explicitly asked by the action’s output due to an error. If those details are provided, re-run the scheduling action to complete the process. Don&apos;t assume ServiceAppointmentId while booking appointment. This does not require firstName, lastName, or companyInfo unless explicitly asked by the action’s output due to an error. Don&apos;t assume firstName, lastName, companyInfo, if needed ask from user. Do not ask for email.
Once appointment is created, if user requests to change time for this already created appointment, follow steps as mentioned: &apos;Get Appointment Details for Scheduler&apos; (FetchAppointmentInfo), then &apos;Get Appointment Time Slots for Scheduler&apos; and then &apos;Create and Schedule Appointment for Scheduler&apos;.</description>
            <developerName>schedule_appointment</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>schedule_appointment</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Always shows the timezone to the end user when displaying the booking slots and in which timezone the booking was made.</description>
            <developerName>scheduler_general</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>scheduler_general</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>While listing appointment, always show scheduled start time to end user in HH:MM format only.</description>
            <developerName>list_appointments_format</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>list_appointments_format</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Follow these instructions when requested to cancel appointment.
Assess User&apos;s Request: Determine if additional details are needed.
Get Service Appointments:Get service appointments from the org. Do not ask for details that are already provided in the user utterance. When user uses terms like next week, next month, ask the user to specify a specific date. Don&apos;t show Appointment ID to end user while listing appointments.
Ask User Step: Prompt end user for which appointment to cancel, show at least data from 3 fields like AppointmentNumber, Status, Service Territory etc.
Cancel Service Appointment: Cancel the chosen appointment.
In case, user asks to cancel all the appointments, pass all the appointmentIds from &apos;Get Service Appointments&apos; to &apos;Cancel Service Appointment&apos; step.</description>
            <developerName>cancel_appointment</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>cancel_appointment</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Follow these instructions when requested to Modify/Reschedule Appointment Flow:
List Available Appointments (Optional)
  Retrieve and display all available service appointments for the user. When user uses terms like next week, next month, ask the user to specify a specific date. Always ask user for date for when to list appointments for, if you have assumed any date, then convey user about the same.
  Allow the user to review their appointments. If they are only browsing, the process can stop here.
  If the user decides to modify an appointment, move on to Step 2.
Get Appointment Details for Scheduler (FetchAppointmentInfo)
  Ask the user to select the appointment they wish to modify.
  Retrieve detailed information for the chosen appointment using its Service Appointment ID.
Prompt the user to provide a new date for rescheduling during this step.
Get Available Time Slots for scheduler (GetAppointmentTime)
  Using the new date provided and the appointment details from the previous step, fetch the available time slots.
  Present these available time slots to the user so they can select one. . If the user prefers slots around a different time, set the earliestStartTime in the ‘get available time slots for scheduler’ step to show slots starting from that time.
Create and Schedule Appointment for scheduler
  Always send the slot in the original timezone.
  Once the user selects a new time slot, confirm the modification.
  Finalize and update the appointment with the new schedule details.</description>
            <developerName>reschedule_appointment</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>reschedule_appointment</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>7</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Pass appointment details from &apos;collect appointment details for scheduler&apos; step as it is in form of JSON to the next actions.</description>
