        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Autonomously coordinates equipment replacement when asset health thresholds are breached. Reads breach details, diagnoses from AssetAttribute values, creates replacement case, and notifies customer.</description>
        <developerName>VDD_Proactive_Health_Monitor_16jaj000002C0uL</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Route to this topic when an asset threshold monitoring alert fires (RecordsetFltrCritMonitor.IsWithinThreshold changes to false).
Step 1: Use Get Threshold Breach Details to identify which threshold was breached, the affected asset, customer, and vehicle.
Step 2: Use Diagnose Asset Health to read all AssetAttribute values and produce a diagnostic summary with severity level and recommended action.
Step 3: Use Create Replacement Case to create a proactive service case and send the customer an SMS notification that the team is already working on the issue.
Always execute all 3 steps in sequence. This is proactive service — act before the customer even knows there is a problem. The goal is zero downtime for the fleet.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_health_monitor</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Proactive Health Monitor Instructions</masterLabel>
